<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><!DOCTYPE article  PUBLIC '-//OASIS//DTD DocBook XML V4.4//EN'  'http://www.docbook.org/xml/4.4/docbookx.dtd'><article><articleinfo><title>ProgrammingGuide/Bootstrap</title><revhistory><revision><revnumber>7</revnumber><date>2011-11-24 22:53:25</date><authorinitials>AmosJeffries</authorinitials><revremark>link back to the developers main page</revremark></revision><revision><revnumber>6</revnumber><date>2009-04-26 04:33:09</date><authorinitials>AmosJeffries</authorinitials><revremark>formatting</revremark></revision><revision><revnumber>5</revnumber><date>2009-04-26 04:25:58</date><authorinitials>AmosJeffries</authorinitials><revremark>libltdl7-dev is not always automatic on Debian and child OS.</revremark></revision><revision><revnumber>4</revnumber><date>2009-04-26 04:22:40</date><authorinitials>AmosJeffries</authorinitials><revremark>this is developer-specific</revremark></revision><revision><revnumber>3</revnumber><date>2008-05-18 19:39:00</date><authorinitials>localhost</authorinitials><revremark>converted to 1.6 markup</revremark></revision><revision><revnumber>2</revnumber><date>2007-12-16 16:31:06</date><authorinitials>ecasbas</authorinitials><revremark>One more error and solution in sourcebootstrap</revremark></revision></revhistory></articleinfo><para>The <emphasis role="strong">bootstrap.sh</emphasis> script runs a number of autotools to prepare ./configure and related magic. See <ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/ProgrammingGuide/Bootstrap/DeveloperResources#">DeveloperResources</ulink> for the tools required by this script. </para><para>It doesn't always work.  Here are some errors and solutions: </para><section><title>LIBTOOL undefined</title><itemizedlist><listitem override="none"><para>Prior to Squid-3.0: </para></listitem></itemizedlist><para><emphasis role="underline">Problem</emphasis> </para><screen><![CDATA[  src/cppunit/Makefile.am:8: Libtool library used but `LIBTOOL' is undefined]]></screen><para><emphasis role="underline">Solution</emphasis> </para><screen><![CDATA[  echo '/usr/local/share/aclocal' >> /usr/local/share/aclocal19/dirlist]]></screen></section><section><title>possibly undefined macro: AC_DISABLE_SHARED</title><para><emphasis role="underline">Problem</emphasis> </para><screen><![CDATA[  configure.in:33: error: possibly undefined macro: AC_DISABLE_SHARED
  configure.in:34: error: possibly undefined macro: AC_PROG_LIBTOOL
  configure.in:35: error: possibly undefined macro: AC_LTDL_DLLIB]]></screen><para><emphasis role="underline">Solution</emphasis> </para><screen><![CDATA[  echo '/usr/local/share/aclocal' >> /usr/local/share/aclocal19/dirlist]]></screen></section><section><title>Can't locate object method &quot;path&quot; via package &quot;Request&quot;</title><para><emphasis role="underline">Problem</emphasis> </para><screen><![CDATA[    Can't locate object method "path" via package "Request" at /usr/local/share/autoconf259/Autom4te/C4che.pm]]></screen><para><emphasis role="underline">Solution</emphasis> </para><itemizedlist><listitem override="none"><para>rm -rf autom4te.cache </para></listitem></itemizedlist></section><section><title>possibly undefined macro: AC_LTDL_DLLIB</title><itemizedlist><listitem override="none"><para>Generally in Debian based systems: </para></listitem></itemizedlist><para><emphasis role="underline">Problem</emphasis> </para><screen><![CDATA[    configure.in:34 error: possibly undefined macro: AC_LTDL_DLLIB
          If this token and others are legitimate, please use m4_pattern_allow.
          See the Autoconf documentation.]]></screen><para><emphasis role="underline">Solution</emphasis> </para><itemizedlist><listitem override="none"><para>install libltdl3-dev or libltdl7-dev </para></listitem></itemizedlist></section><section><title>'ltdl.m4' not found in '/usr/share/aclocal'</title><itemizedlist><listitem override="none"><para>Generally in Debian based systems: </para></listitem></itemizedlist><para><emphasis role="underline">Problem</emphasis> </para><screen><![CDATA[    libtoolize: 'ltdl.m4' not found in '/usr/share/aclocal'
    libtoolize failed
    Autotool bootstrapping failed. You will need to investigate and correct
    before you can develop on this source tree]]></screen><para><emphasis role="underline">Solution</emphasis> </para><itemizedlist><listitem override="none"><para>install libltdl7-dev </para></listitem></itemizedlist></section></article>